            <h2>
                   <strong> Scholarship Description:</strong>
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        Bigyani Kanya Medha Britti Scholarship is an initiative to encourage girl child to study further after completing her 12th class in West Bengal. This scholarship is provided to girls who want to study higher after their 12th but do not have sufficient funds to carry on their higher studies. Girls studying from any board and any stream be it Basic Science/Medicine/Non-medical in West Bengal are eligible for this scholarship scheme. The scholarship shall be awarded by Jagadis Bose National Science Talent Search (JBNSTS), Kolkata. Under this unique initiative girls will get exposed the world of education and can pursue their dreams with the help of this scholarship 
The scholarship amount given by JBNSTS is exponentially good. The student will be provided Rs 2000 per month for 5 years in order to complete her higher education. Secondly, the student will also be given Rs 2000 per annum as a yearly book grant. Besides, the girl will be provided with free academic and career counseling plus participation in seminars and colloquia. Travel and Enrichment programs will also be taken care of along with the project work.

                           </p>
                            <h2>
                                <hr>
                                    <strong>Eligibility for the Scholarship:</strong>
                                    </h2>
 <p>
 
The eligibility criteria for the scholarship are as follows
<ul>
<li> Indian National Girlfrom West Bengal who has passed the Higher Secondary or equivalent examination in the year of application.</li>
<li>The Girl must have passed 12th class in 2018 from any Board and studying Basic Science/Medicine/ Engineering in any institute of West Bengal.</li>
<li> Only girls have enrolled in some undergraduate program after 12th class can apply for this scholarship.</li>
<li> Diploma course students are not eligible, only degree courses students should apply.</li>
</ul>
</p>
